About:
My goal in life is to have a positive impact on society. I believe I can do this by leveraging my technical skills to help people become more efficient and to help them make better decisions. Although I'm analytical/scientific by nature, I enjoy applying a zen-like attitude towards work and life.

I recently quit my job after ~10 years in the corporate world. Although I was on successful track, I realized that it wasn't for me. The money was good, but I wasn't achieving my true calling. As a result, I resigned and started up my own software company. It's been a huge change, but definitely for the better. In a month's time (June, 2013), I plan on throwing my laptop in my backpack, jumping on my motorcycle and heading out to Silicon Valley. I figure if I'm going to swing for the fences, might as well be in the right ballpark.
